can find the list of notes.</p>\n<h2>Endpoint 2: Files List</h2>\n<p><code>/api/files.json</code> returns an array of all notes with their metadata:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-json\">{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"slug\": \"...\",\n      \"url\": \"...\",\n      \"title\": \"...\",\n      \"date\": \"...\",\n      \"excerpt\": \"...\",\n      \"tags\": [...]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"...\"\n}\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Endpoint 3: Individual Note</h2>\n<p><code>/api/notes/[slug]</code> returns the raw markdown file with frontmatter intact. This is important because other clients might want to parse it themselves.</p>\n<h2>CORS Headers</h2>\n<p>Added CORS headers to all endpoints so they can be consumed by other developers' clients. This is key for the decentralized approach.</p>\n</div></main><footer class=\"footer\"><p>Built with Next.js • Deployed on Vercel</p></footer></div><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/webpack-c8441f2d519541e3.js\" async=\"\"></script><script>(self.__next_f=self.__next_f||[]).push([0]);self.__next_f.push([2,null])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"1:HL[\\\"/_next/static/css/d753f4838feb0173.css\\\",\\\"style\\\"]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"2:I[2846,[],\\\"\\\"]\\n5:I[4707,[],\\\"\\\"]\\n7:I[6423,[],\\\"\\\"]\\n9:I[1060,[],\\\"\\\"]\\n6:[\\\"slug\\\",\\\"2024-01-16-api-endpoints\\\",\\\"d\\\"]\\na:[]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"0:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L2\\\",null,{\\\"buildId\\\":\\\"_uB49DAU_UWYsY4PWCQH2\\\",\\\"assetPrefix\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlParts\\\":[\\\"\\\",\\\"notes\\\",\\\"2024-01-16-api-endpoints\\\"],\\\"initialTree\\\":[\\\"\\\",{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"notes\\\",{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"slug\\\",\\\"2024-01-16-api-endpoints\\\",\\\"d\\\"],{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"__PAGE__?{\\\\\\\"slug\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"2024-01-16-api-endpoints\\\\\\\"}\\\",{}]}]}]},\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"$undefined\\\",true],\\\"initialSeedData\\\":[\\\"\\\",{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"notes\\\",{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"slug